detail_description: Il Gallo D'Oro is a renowned fine dining restaurant located in The Cliff Bay hotel in Funchal, Madeira. This upscale establishment has been awarded two Michelin stars and is celebrated as the best restaurant on the island and even throughout Portugal at times. Specializing in Iberian Cuisine, Il Gallo D'Oro prides itself on using locally sourced produce to ensure the freshness and quality of its dishes.
name: Il Gallo D'Oro
address: The Cliff Bay hotel, Estrada Monumental 147, São Martinho, 9004-532 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Vila do Peixe is a seafood restaurant located in the lively Camara de Lobos, just a short drive from Funchal. The restaurant offers a live fish counter where diners can select their own fresh seafood, including tuna, sea bream, and black scabbard fish. These are simply grilled with salt and served alongside stunning views of the city and bay through floor-to-ceiling windows.
name: Restaurante Vila do Peixe
address: R. Dr. João Abel de Freitas 30A, 9300-048 Câmara de Lobos, Portugal

detail_description: Armazém do Sal is a charming restaurant located in the heart of Funchal, Portugal, housed within a former salt warehouse. The restaurant boasts an inviting ambiance with wooden beams and stone walls. It offers a small but dedicated vegan menu featuring three main dishes including soya moussaka with roasted aubergine, lentil salad with roasted vegetables, and barley salad with caramelized baby vegetables.
name: Armazém do Sal - Michelin Guide 2024
address: R. da Alfândega 135, São Martinho, 9000-059 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Lá ao Fundo is a must-visit in Funchal's Old Town, offering a unique gastronomic experience with its fusion of Mediterranean, European, Portuguese, and modern cuisine. The restaurant boasts a welcoming and laid-back ambiance that makes diners feel at home.
name: Restaurante Lá ao Fundo
address: R. Portão de São Tiago 17A, 9060-250 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Design Centre Nini Andrade Silva is a must-visit attraction for those seeking a unique and immersive experience. The center features stunning gardens that seamlessly blend with nature, providing visitors with an unforgettable environment. It also houses an innovative museum designed by renowned architect Paulo David, showcasing gravity-defying contemporary architecture that contrasts beautifully with the traditional island surroundings. Inside, visitors can explore exhibition spaces, workshops, and a museum for study purposes.
name: Design Centre Nini Andrade Silva
address: Estrada da Pontinha, Forte de Nossa Senhora da Conceição, 9000-726 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Desarma is a contemporary restaurant that focuses on the simplicity and flavor of food. The chef's expertise shines through in every dish, creating a unique dining experience. The restaurant offers both 6 and 9 course menus, featuring a blend of local cuisine with innovative twists. Guests are impressed by the impressive open kitchen and stunning views over Funchal bay. The attentive and professional staff adds to the overall exceptional dining experience at Restaurante Desarma.
name: Restaurante Desarma
address: The Views Baía, R. das Maravilhas 74, 9000-177 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Museu Café & Petisco is a charming cafe and bar located near the Museu de Arte Sacra in Funchal. The chef draws inspiration from Portuguese and Madeiran ingredients as well as international flavors, resulting in delicious and lovingly prepared food. The lunch menu changes daily, offering a variety of options at great value. With outdoor seating facing the main square, it's an ideal spot to enjoy coffee, cocktails, or a satisfying meal.
name: Museu Café & Petisco
address: Praca do Município 85, São Martinho, 9000-043 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled in the enchanting heart of Funchal's old town, William Restaurant is a true gem that embodies elegance and sophistication. Set within a beautifully restored 18th-century mansion, this Michelin-starred dining destination invites guests on an exquisite culinary adventure that celebrates the rich flavors of Madeira. With stunning views overlooking Porto de Funchal, diners can savor innovative dishes crafted from the finest local ingredients while enjoying a contemporary twist on traditional European cuisine.
name: William Restaurant
address: Estrada Monumental 139, São Martinho, 9000-098 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Avista Restaurant, located within Les Suites at Cliff Bay, offers a unique dining experience with its Mediterranean and Asian cuisine overseen by chef Benoit Sinthon. The restaurant's century-old house setting provides a charming backdrop for enjoying the diverse menu options, including a la carte dishes designed for sharing and bistro-style tasting menus. With its Michelin-starred quality and stunning views of the Atlantic Ocean, Avista is celebrated as one of Funchal's top dining destinations.
name: Avista Restaurant
address: Estrada Monumental 145, São Martinho, 9004-532 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Casal da Penha is a charming, family-owned restaurant located in the heart of Funchal. The traditional Madeiran and Portuguese dishes served here include bolo do caco, black scabbard fish with bananas, Madeiran-style tuna, espetada, and passionfruit pudding with Madeira wines. The restaurant also offers a daily variety of fresh fish and seafood purchased at the local market.
name: Restaurante Casal da Penha
address: Beco da Ataíde 1, São Martinho, 9000-604 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Barreirinha Bar Café is a popular spot in Funchal, located just 4km outside of the town center. It offers a versatile experience, serving as a cafe during the day and transforming into a lively bar at night. The menu features easy-to-eat items such as burgers, sandwiches, burritos, and salads. The location on a hillside provides stunning views of the ocean from small outside tables on the terrace.
name: Barreirinha Bar Café
address: Largo do Socorro 1, 9060-305 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: In Funchal, the Allegro Madeira Adults Only hotel offers great value for money with its stunning panoramic views of the Atlantic Ocean. The hotel's 124 bright rooms are decorated in blue tones and it is conveniently located close to the historic center and the area of Lido. Guests can enjoy traditional and international cuisine at the hotel's restaurant, as well as delicious cocktails at the Rooftop Bar 360 while taking in the horizon view.
name: Restaurante Atlantic
address: Estrada Monumental 179, São Martinho, 9000-100 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Local Shop is a charming bar and cafe located in Monte, offering a selection of local craft beers and delicious coffee. Despite its proximity to the Monte cable car, it manages to maintain an authentic atmosphere without being overly touristy. The outdoor seating area provides stunning views of the valley, making it an ideal spot to relax and enjoy a drink or snack. Visitors praise the friendly staff and recommend stopping by for a coffee and homemade cake deal.
name: LocalShop
address: Quiosque do Teleférico do Jardim Botânico / Babosas, Largo das Babosas, Monte, 9050-542 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: The Golden Gate Grand Cafe is a classic and elegant dining spot located in the heart of Funchal, offering a glimpse into the traditional Madeira atmosphere. Situated at the lower level of Hotel Quinta da Casa Branca, this luxurious Manor House features a distinctive dining room with an al fresco terrace. Established since 1814, it provides a charming ambiance for patrons to enjoy Portuguese dishes or British-style afternoon tea.
name: Golden Gate Grand Cafe
address: Av. Arriaga N° 29, São Martinho, 9000-060 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled in a picturesque location with stunning ocean views, Cris's Place is a highly recommended restaurant in Madeira known for its gourmet European cuisine. The well-curated menu features locally sourced ingredients and is updated twice a year, offering Instagram-worthy dishes that are as visually appealing as they are delicious. The restaurant boasts a lovely terrace and floor-to-ceiling windows, allowing guests to enjoy the scenic surroundings both indoors and outdoors.
name: Cris's Place
address: R. da Casa Branca 34A, São Martinho, 9000-088 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Located in Funchal, Madeira Island, Loja do Chá is a beloved destination for tea lovers. Since 2003, this charming teahouse and café has been offering an extensive selection of around 200 different teas and infusions known for their exceptional quality and unique character. Whether you're a tea enthusiast or just looking to explore new flavors, the diverse range of international teas available here is sure to captivate your senses.
name: Loja do Chá
address: R. do Sabão 33 35, São Martinho, 9000-056 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante do Forte is a dining establishment located within the historic Sao Tiago Fortress, offering a unique and memorable experience. The restaurant boasts a diverse menu featuring both local and international dishes, with spectacular views of the harbor adding to the ambiance. The setting within the 17th-century fortress creates an elegant atmosphere, making it an ideal choice for a special evening out.
name: Restaurante do Forte
address: Tv. do Forte 3, 9060-123 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled on the 16th floor of the Savoy Palace, Galáxia Skyfood offers a dining experience that feels like an enchanting journey among the stars. The restaurant's cozy ambiance features beautifully painted ceilings, setting the stage for Chef Carlos Goncalves' innovative five- to seven-course tasting menus.
name: Galáxia Skyfood | Skybar
address: Av. do Infante 25, São Martinho, 9004-542 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: The Wanderer is a unique restaurant in Funchal that draws inspiration from the extensive travels of its owner, who has explored more than 100 countries. The diverse menu showcases culinary delights from various parts of the world, encompassing dishes like Indian curry, Thai pad thai, and Lebanese falafel. Offering a vibrant array of flavors and aromas, this establishment prides itself on sourcing fresh and top-notch ingredients locally.
name: The Wanderer
address: Centro Comercial Olimpo, Av. do Infante, São Martinho, 9000-015 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Modern choice with outdoor seating & an open kitchen offering sustainable, elevated dishes.
detail_description: Kampo by Chef Julio Pereira is a modern restaurant with outdoor seating and an open kitchen, offering sustainable and elevated dishes. Located in Funchal, Portugal, the restaurant provides a unique dining experience with a focus on seafood and meatier options. Chef Julio Pereira's creative menu includes fish charcuterie boards, braised tuna with razor clam rice, grouper carpaccio with nori, as well as other innovative dishes.
name: Kampo by Chef Julio Pereira
address: R. da Alfândega 74, São Martinho, 9000-059 Funchal, Portugal
